[SN]TITLE[SN]
Frank Auerbach: Is he the UK's greatest living artist?

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Frank Auerbach has been called "the country's greatest living artist" and a major retrospective of his work opened at Tate Britain in London on Friday.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
12 October 2015 Last updated at 12:33 BST
Auerbach - who is now 84 - could name painters Lucian Freud and Francis Bacon as his friends. Unlike them, his life has been austere and modest.
In a rare and exclusive interview, he's been talking to Newsnight's culture correspondent Stephen Smith.
